<sawd:dashboardPage xmlns:sawd="com.siebel.analytics.web/dashboard/v1.1" xmlns:saw="com.siebel.analytics.web/report/v1.1" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlVersion="200810300" isEmpty="false" duid="mi9t3l46jnjo1ac2"><sawd:dashboardColumn name="Column 0" frozen="false" canFreeze="true" duid="iilthda1utgivqno" layoutType="bestFit"><sawd:dashboardSection name="Section 0" duid="46gul9in4mgthild" showSectionTitle="false" horizontalLayout="true" showHeading="false" layoutType="bestFit"><saw:caption><saw:text>Explanation</saw:text></saw:caption><sawd:htmlView name="HTML 3" duid="qobt66nm1m1lnj0d"><sawd:HTML fmt="html">[b]The Reason:[/b][br/]
Following are two important aspects of designing for accessible navigation that require changes from the default layout you get:[br/]
[br/]
1) The difference between using the default section layout versus creating visible names for each dashboard section.[br/]
2) How to preserve the dashboard context when drilling into one of the objects on a dashboard page.[br/]
[br/]
Neither of these design requirements is included in a dashboard by default. They are easy to add, but [b][i]must be[/i][/b] explicitly defined [br/]by the content designer by using the included properties available in the Dashboard Editor.[br/]
[br/]
[i](The initial state of this dashboard represents the default settings, so you can see what needs to be changed [br/]in order to fully enable accessible screen navigation.)[/i]</sawd:HTML></sawd:htmlView><sawd:htmlView name="HTML 4" duid="sl4mafns6o8vtf27"><sawd:HTML fmt="html">[b]How-To:[/b][br/]
[u]Named Sections[/u][br/]
1) Launch the dashboard editor[br/]
2) Hover over each Section and click on the Section [b]Properties[/b] menu[br/]
3) Click on the [b]Rename...[/b] menu and enter a name for the section[br/]
4) Click on the Section [b]Properties[/b] menu again[br/]
5) Click on the [b]Show Section Header[/b] and [b]Show Section Title[/b] menu items to turn them on.[br/]
[br/]
[u]Drilling in Place[/u][br/]
6) Click on the Section [b]Properties[/b] menu again[br/]
7) Click on the [b]Drill in Place[/b] menu item to turn it on.[br/]
